											<h2 class="entry-title">WHAT WE DO</h2>
					
					<div class="entry-content">
						<p style="text-align: left;">The REDD Fast Logging Assessment &amp; Monitoring Environment (REDD-FLAME) project will design, prototype and demonstrate a system capable of monitoring tropical and sub-tropical forests using high-resolution radar (and optical) imagery acquired by Earth Observation satellites. By focusing on early detection of logging activities, the system will provide the means to quickly identify the first signs of deforestation and thus act as a tool to control resource use and sustainable development within these fragile and valuable environments.</p>
